HEADWORD: Hotel
<hw>Ho*tel"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>h⟦ocir⟧tel</ets>, OF. <ets>hostel</ets>. See
<er>Hostel</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A house for entertaining
strangers or travelers; an inn or public house, of the better
class.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>In France, the mansion or town residence of a person
of rank or wealth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hotel-de-ville</ent>⟦br⟧
